Holy Word(Player's Handbook v.3.5): - Good(7)
	/w gm &{template:DnD35StdRoll} {{spellflag=true}} {{name=@{character_name}}} {{subtags=casts [Holy Word](https://dndtools.net/spells/players-handbook-v35--6/holy-word--2623/) }} {{School:= Evocation  [Good][Sonic]}} {{Level:= **Good 7**, Cleric 7, Elysium 7, Mysticism 7, Cloistered Cleric 7}} {{Components:= V}} {{Range:= 40 ft.}} {{Area:=Nongood creatures in a 40-ft.-radius spread centered on you}} {{Duration:=Instantaneous}} {{Savingthrow:=None or Will negates; see text }} {{Save DC:=[[@{spelldc7}+@{sf-Evocation}]]}} {{Spellresistance:=Yes }} {{CLC:= [[ 1d20+@{casterlevel2}+@{spellpen} ]] vs spell resistance.}} {{compcheck=Concentration: [[ {1d20+ [[ @{concentration} ]] }>[[?{Damage Taken|0}+15+0]] ]] }} {{succeedcheck=Success! @{subjective} casts @{possessive} spell!}} {{failcheck=@{subjective} fails @{possessive} concentration :( }} {{notes=Any nongood creature within the area that hears the holy word suffers the following ill effects.
The effects are cumulative and concurrent.
